It is decidable whether a list is null or not 
S:Type
l:list S
Decision (l = [])


S:Type
l:list S
Decision (l = [])

  destruct l; [left; reflexivity|right; congruence].
Qed.
A list is either null or it can be decomposed into an initial prefix and a last element 
S:Type
l:list S
l = [] \/
(exists (l' : list S) (a : S), l = l' ++ [a])


S:Type
l:list S
l = [] \/
(exists (l' : list S) (a : S), l = l' ++ [a])

  
S:Type
l:list S
e:l = []
l = [] \/
(exists (l' : list S) (a : S), l = l' ++ [a])
S:Type
l:list S
n:l <> []
l = [] \/
(exists (l' : list S) (a : S), l = l' ++ [a])

  
S:Type
l:list S
e:l = []
l = [] \/
(exists (l' : list S) (a : S), l = l' ++ [a])
 
S:Type
l:list S
e:l = []
l = []
 assumption.
  
S:Type
l:list S
n:l <> []
l = [] \/
(exists (l' : list S) (a : S), l = l' ++ [a])
 
S:Type
l:list S
n:l <> []
exists (l' : list S) (a : S), l = l' ++ [a]
 
S:Type
l:list S
n:{l' : list S & {a : S | l = l' ++ [a]}}
exists (l' : list S) (a : S), l = l' ++ [a]
 
S:Type
l, l':list S
a:S
Heq:l = l' ++ [a]
exists (l' : list S) (a : S), l = l' ++ [a]

    
S:Type
l, l':list S
a:S
Heq:l = l' ++ [a]
exists a : S, l = l' ++ [a]
 
S:Type
l, l':list S
a:S
Heq:l = l' ++ [a]
l = l' ++ [a]
 assumption.
Qed.
destructs a list in @l@ in either null or a prefix @l'@ and a last element @a@ with an equation @Heq@ stating that @l = l' ++ a@ 
Ltac destruct_list_last l l' a Heq := destruct (null_or_exists_last l) as [Heq | [l' [a Heq]]]; rewrite Heq in *.


S:Type
l:list S
a:S
l ++ [a] <> []


S:Type
l:list S
a:S
l ++ [a] <> []

  
S:Type
l:list S
a:S
contra:l ++ [a] = []
False
 destruct l; discriminate contra.
Qed.

Definition last_error {S} (l : list S) : option S :=
  match l with
  | [] => None
  | a :: t => Some (last t a)
  end.


S:Type
forall (random a b : S) (l : list S),
last (a :: b :: l) random = last (b :: l) random


S:Type
forall (random a b : S) (l : list S),
last (a :: b :: l) random = last (b :: l) random

  
S:Type
random, h1, h2:S
tl:list S
last (h1 :: h2 :: tl) random = last (h2 :: tl) random

  
S:Type
random, h1, h2:S
tl:list S
match tl with
| [] => h2
| _ :: _ =>
    (fix last (l : list S) (d : S) {struct l} : S :=
       match l with
       | [] => d
       | [a] => a
       | a :: (_ :: _) as l1 => last l1 d
       end) tl random
end =
match tl with
| [] => h2
| _ :: _ =>
    (fix last (l : list S) (d : S) {struct l} : S :=
       match l with
       | [] => d
       | [a] => a
       | a :: (_ :: _) as l1 => last l1 d
       end) tl random
end
 reflexivity.
Qed.


S:Type

last (a :: b :: c :: l) random =
last (b :: a :: c :: l) random


S:Type
forall (random a b c : S) (l : list S),
last (a :: b :: c :: l) random =
last (b :: a :: c :: l) random

  
S:Type

tl:list S
last (h1 :: h2 :: s :: tl) random =
last (h2 :: h1 :: s :: tl) random

  
S:Type

S:Type

tl:list S
IHl:last (h1 :: h2 :: s :: tl) random =
last (h2 :: h1 :: s :: tl) random

tl:list S
IHl:last (h1 :: h2 :: s :: tl) random =
last (h2 :: h1 :: s :: tl) random

S:Type
random, h1, h2, s, hd:S
tl:list S
IHl:last (h1 :: h2 :: s :: tl) random =
last (h2 :: h1 :: s :: tl) random
match tl with
| [] => hd
| _ :: _ => last tl random
end =
match tl with
| [] => hd
| _ :: _ => last tl random
end
 reflexivity.
Qed.

A:Type

def:A
last (l1 ++ l2) def = last l2 (last l1 def)

last (l1 ++ l2) def = last l2 (last l1 def)

  
A:Type

last (l1 ++ l2) def = last l2 (last l1 def)

last (l1 ++ l2) def = last l2 (last l1 def)

last l2 (last (a :: l1) def)

Qed.

forall (A : Type) (f : A -> bool) (x : A) (s : list A),
In x s -> f x = true -> In x (filter f s)


forall (A : Type) (f : A -> bool) (x : A) (s : list A),
In x s -> f x = true -> In x (filter f s)

x:A

H:In x s
H0:f x = true
In x (filter f s)
 
A:Type
f:A -> bool
x:A
s:list A
H:In x s
H0:f x = true
In x s /\ f x = true
 split; assumption.
Qed.

Qed.

forall (A : Type) (x y : A) (l : list A),
In x l -> ~ In y l -> x <> y


forall (A : Type) (x y : A) (l : list A),
In x l -> ~ In y l -> x <> y

  
A:Type
x, y:A
l:list A
H:In x l
H0:~ In y l
x <> y
 
A:Type
y:A
l:list A
H:In y l
H0:~ In y l
False
 
A:Type
y:A
l:list A
H:In y l
H0:~ In y l
In y l
 assumption.
Qed.

Definition inb {A} (Aeq_dec : forall x y:A, {x = y} + {x <> y}) (x : A) (xs : list A) :=
  if in_dec Aeq_dec x xs then true else false.


A:Type
Aeq_dec:forall x y : A, {x = y} + {x <> y}
PredicateFunction2 (In (A:=A)) (inb Aeq_dec)


A:Type
Aeq_dec:forall x y : A, {x = y} + {x <> y}
PredicateFunction2 (In (A:=A)) (inb Aeq_dec)

  
A:Type
Aeq_dec:forall x y : A, {x = y} + {x <> y}
x:A
xs:list A
In x xs <-> inb Aeq_dec x xs = true
 
A:Type
Aeq_dec:forall x y : A, {x = y} + {x <> y}
x:A
xs:list A
In x xs <->
(if in_dec Aeq_dec x xs then true else false) = true
 destruct (in_dec Aeq_dec x xs); split; intros
  ; try assumption; try reflexivity; try contradiction; discriminate.
Qed.

Definition inclb
  `{EqDecision A}
  (l1 l2 : list A)
  : bool
  := forallb (fun x : A => inb decide_eq x l2) l1.


A:Type
EqDecision0:EqDecision A
PredicateFunction2 (incl (A:=A)) inclb


A:Type
EqDecision0:EqDecision A
PredicateFunction2 (incl (A:=A)) inclb

  
A:Type
EqDecision0:EqDecision A
l1, l2:list A
incl l1 l2 <-> inclb l1 l2 = true
 
A:Type
EqDecision0:EqDecision A
l1, l2:list A
incl l1 l2 <->
forallb (fun x : A => inb decide_eq x l2) l1 = true
 
A:Type
EqDecision0:EqDecision A
l1, l2:list A
incl l1 l2 <->
(forall x : A, In x l1 -> inb decide_eq x l2 = true)

  split; intros Hincl x Hx; apply in_correct; apply Hincl; assumption.
Qed.

Definition incl_correct `{EqDecision A}
  (l1 l2 : list A)
  : incl l1 l2 <-> inclb l1 l2 = true
  := incl_function l1 l2.

Definition app_cons {A}
  (a : A)
  (l : list A)
  : [a] ++ l = a :: l
  := eq_refl.

(forall a : A, In a l2 -> ~ In a l1) ->
NoDup (l1 ++ l2)
l2:list A
H0:NoDup l2
H1:forall a0 : A, a = a0 \/ In a0 l1 -> ~ In a0 l2
H2:forall a0 : A, In a0 l2 -> ~ (a = a0 \/ In a0 l1)
H5:~ In a l1
H6:NoDup l1
InL2:In a l2
False

Polymorphic list library 
Fixpoint is_member {W} `{StrictlyComparable W} (w : W) (l : list W) : bool :=
  match l with
  | [] => false
  | hd :: tl => match compare w hd with
              | Eq => true
              | _ => is_member w tl
              end
  end.

Definition compareb {A} `{StrictlyComparable A} (a1 a2 : A) : bool :=
  match compare a1 a2 with
  | Eq => true
  | _ => false
  end.

X:Type
forall (l1 l2 : list X) (x : X),
In x (l1 ++ l2) <-> In x (l2 ++ l1)


X:Type
forall (l1 l2 : list X) (x : X),
In x (l1 ++ l2) <-> In x (l2 ++ l1)

  intros l1 l2 x; split; intro H_in;
  apply in_or_app; apply in_app_or in H_in;
    destruct H_in as [cat | dog];
    tauto.
Qed.

Fixpoint list_suffix
  {A : Type}
  (l : list A)
  (n : nat)
  : list A
  := match n,l with
    | 0,_ => l
    | _,[] => []
    | S n, a :: l => list_suffix l n
    end.


A, B:Type
f:A -> B
l:list A

list_suffix (map f (a :: l)) (S n)

Fixpoint list_prefix
  {A : Type}
  (l : list A)
  (n : nat)
  : list A
  := match n,l with
    | 0,_ => []
    | _,[] => []
    | S n, a :: l => a :: list_prefix l n
    end.

   (A : Type) (l : list A) (n : nat) {struct l} :
     list A :=
   match n with
   | 0 => []
   | S n0 =>
       match l with
       | [] => []
       | a :: l0 => a :: list_prefix A l0 n0
       end
   end) A l 0 = []

    destruct l;
    reflexivity.

Definition list_segment
  {A : Type}
  (l : list A)
  (n1 n2 : nat)
  := list_suffix (list_prefix l n2) n1.

list_annotate:forall (A : Type) (P : A -> Prop)
  (l : list A),
Forall P l -> list {x : A | P x}
A:Type

a:A
l:list A

list {x : A | P x}

  exact ((exist P a (Forall_hd Hs)) :: list_annotate A P l (Forall_tl Hs)).
Defined.


A:Type
P:A -> Prop
a:A
l:list A
Hs:Forall P (a :: l)
list_annotate P (a :: l) Hs =
exist P a (Forall_hd Hs)
:: list_annotate P l (Forall_tl Hs)


A:Type
P:A -> Prop
a:A
l:list A
Hs:Forall P (a :: l)
list_annotate P (a :: l) Hs =
exist P a (Forall_hd Hs)
:: list_annotate P l (Forall_tl Hs)

  reflexivity.
Qed.

Fixpoint nth_error_filter_index
  {A}
  (f : A -> bool)
  (l : list A)
  (n : nat)
  :=
  match l with
  | [] => None
  | a :: l =>
    match f a with
    | false => option_map S (nth_error_filter_index f l n)
    | true =>
      match n with
      | 0 => Some 0
      | S n => option_map S (nth_error_filter_index f l n)
      end
    end
  end.


A:Type
f:A -> bool
l:list A
n1, n2:nat
Hle:n1 <= n2
in1, in2:nat
Hin1:nth_error_filter_index f l n1 = Some in1
Hin2:nth_error_filter_index f l n2 = Some in2
in1 <= in2


A:Type
f:A -> bool
l:list A
n1, n2:nat
Hle:n1 <= n2
in1, in2:nat
Hin1:nth_error_filter_index f l n1 = Some in1
Hin2:nth_error_filter_index f l n2 = Some in2
in1 <= in2

  
A:Type

l:list A
n1, n2:nat
Hle:n1 <= n2
in1:nat
Hin1:nth_error_filter_index f l n1 = Some in1
forall in2 : nat,
nth_error_filter_index f l n2 = Some in2 -> in1 <= in2

Definition map_option
  {A B : Type}
  (f : A -> option B)
  : list A -> list B
  :=
  fold_right
    (fun x lb =>
      match f x with
      | None => lb
      | Some b => b :: lb
      end
    )
    [].


A, B:Type
f:A -> option B
l:list A
Hfl:Forall (fun a : A => f a <> None) l
length (map_option f l) = length l

Fixpoint one_element_decompositions
  {A : Type}
  (l : list A)
  : list (list A * A * list A)
  :=
  match l with
  | [] => []
  | a :: l' =>
    ([], a, l')
    :: map
      (fun t => match t with (l1, b, l2) => (a :: l1, b, l2) end)
      (one_element_decompositions l')
  end.


A:Type
l, pre, suf:list A
x:A
In (pre, x, suf) (one_element_decompositions l) <->
pre ++ [x] ++ suf = l

pre ++ [x] ++ suf = l

pre ++ [x] ++ suf = l

In (pre, x, suf) (one_element_decompositions l) <->
pre ++ [x] ++ suf = l

Definition two_element_decompositions
  {A : Type}
  (l : list A)
  : list (list A * A * list A * A * list A)
  :=
  flat_map
    (fun t =>
      match t with
        (l1, e1, l2) =>
        map
          (fun t => match t with (l2',e2, l3) => (l1, e1, l2', e2, l3) end)
          (one_element_decompositions l2)
      end
    )
    (one_element_decompositions l).


A:Type
l, pre, mid, suf:list A
x, y:A
In (pre, x, mid, y, suf)
  (two_element_decompositions l) <->
pre ++ [x] ++ mid ++ [y] ++ suf = l

         let (y0, l3) := t0 in

        (one_element_decompositions l2))
     (one_element_decompositions l)) <->

elements belonging to first type in a list of a sum type 
Definition list_sum_project_left
  {A B : Type}
  (x : list (A + B))
  : list A
  :=
  map_option sum_project_left x.
elements belonging to second type in a list of a sum type 
Definition list_sum_project_right
  {A B : Type}
  (x : list (A + B))
  : list B
  :=
  map_option sum_project_right x.
